===============================
5.1 From Collections
5.2 From Arrays
5.3 From Static Methods
5.4 Infinite Streams



ğŸ”„ 12. Stream Lazy Evaluation
================================
Streams execute operations only when a terminal operation is invoked. Check coding example for more



ğŸ§ª 13. Common Stream Use Cases
===================================
âœ… Filtering records
âœ… Transforming data
âœ… Removing duplicates
âœ… Aggregating data (sum, count, max, min)
âœ… Grouping or partitioning
âœ… Parallel processing


ğŸ’¡ 14. Complete Example : check the stream_api package
=======================================================

ğŸ§¾ 15. Key Interfaces & Classes
=================================
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
| Interface                                 | Description                                |
| ----------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------ |
| `Stream<T>`                               | Base interface for stream operations       |
| `IntStream`, `LongStream`, `DoubleStream` | Primitive streams                          |
| `Collectors`                              | Utility for collecting results             |
| `Optional<T>`                             | Result container for possibly-empty values |
| `Comparator<T>`                           | For sorting and comparing elements         |
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



